  "title": "Guernsey Is Having a Tortoise Escape Epidemic Right Now",
  "script": "Four tortoises in one day? On the tiny island of Guernsey in the English Channel, the local SPCA had a very strange week — four stray tortoises showed up at their shelter within 24 hours. Just waddled right out of their yards. That's what the GSPCA's manager, Steve Byrne, is calling an epidemic. Here's the thing about tortoises: when temperatures rise, they don't just sit there. They get active. They explore. And the males wander even farther — because they're looking for mates. The GSPCA typically handles 20 to 30 escaped tortoises every summer, but four in one day is unusual even by their standards. And with temperatures still climbing, Steve says more are coming. So is your tortoise still in the yard?",
